CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper December 29, 1951, pg. 13, reads: "Budding Artist - A Promising Art Student and Her Work... Top Middle: Getting some criticism from her classmates - the toughest critics in the world... - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Peggy Owens (Skillen) wearing light colored smock and holding painting to woman and man, in art studio, Carnegie Tech (Carnegie Mellon University)
